                        <provenance type="found" when="1849">The ogham inscription was first noticed in 1849 du G.V. Noyer. The stone was found in the foundations of the chancel of the medieval parish church of St Mary's Gowran (KK020-060006-), when the chancel was demolished in 1827 to make way for a Church of Ireland church (Brash 1872-3; 437; Dolan 2000, vol. 3, 112). The stone had lain prostrate for a long time in the ruined nave (Macalister 1945, 38). </provenance>
