    <text>
        <body>
           <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">
            <ab> 
                <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-up"/><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><supplied reason="lost">ᚋᚐᚊ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ᚔ</unclear></w> <persName>ᚓᚏᚐᚉ<unclear reason="damage">ᚔ</unclear>ᚐᚄ</persName> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><supplied reason="lost">ᚋᚐ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ᚊᚔ</unclear></w> <persName>ᚇ<unclear reason="damage">ᚔ</unclear>ᚋ<unclear reason="damage">ᚐ</unclear>ᚊ<unclear reason="damage">ᚐ</unclear></persName> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋᚒᚉ<unclear reason="damage">ᚑ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ᚔ</supplied></w>
            </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-up"/><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><supplied reason="lost">MAQ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">I</unclear></w> <persName>ERAC<unclear reason="damage">I</unclear>AS</persName> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><supplied reason="lost">MA</supplied><unclear reason="damage">QI</unclear></w> <persName>D<unclear reason="damage">I</unclear>M<unclear reason="damage">A</unclear>Q<unclear reason="damage">A</unclear></persName> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">MUC<unclear reason="damage">O</unclear><supplied reason="lost">I</supplied></w>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app n="1"><note>On the scanned model five notches (I of MAQI) are barely visible before the E of ERACIAS and possibly part of the final Q score. The first two notches of the I after the C in ERACIAS are relatively clear. Also, although there is no trace of the following MA, five partial scores (Q) can be made out on the top of the stone, followed by faint traces of at least three of the five notches of the final I. The vowels of DIMAQA are very unclear but the C of a possible MUCOI and at least one following vowel notch are discernible.</note></app>
                </listApp>               
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>son of X son of Y kindred of ...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription contains formula words commonly found in the ogham corpus such as MAQI, Old Irish <foreign xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31166">macc</ref></foreign>'son' and, according to Stifter (2025), MUCOI which might possibly be related to Old Irish <foreign xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31187">maccu, moccu</ref></foreign> 'belonging to the gens or family of'.</p>
            </div>
